.TH CUSTODIA-ADMIN 1 "@DATE@" "Custodia @VERSION@" "Custodia Manual"
.SH NAME
custodia-admin \- administer a Custodia vault and certificate workflow
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY custodia-admin
.OP --server-url URL
.OP --cert FILE
.OP --key FILE
.OP --ca FILE
.I command
.RI [ arguments ...]
.YS
.SY custodia-admin
.B version
.YS
.SY custodia-admin
.B --version
.YS
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B custodia-admin
is the operator CLI for Custodia. It talks to the vault API over mTLS,
performs metadata-only administration, exports and verifies audit material,
and orchestrates client certificate workflows.
.PP
When the admin certificate and key live under
.I /etc/custodia,
run the command as the restricted
.B custodia
service user, for example:
.PP
.EX
sudo -u custodia custodia-admin --server-url https://localhost:8443 \\
  --cert /etc/custodia/admin.crt \\
  --key /etc/custodia/admin.key \\
  --ca /etc/custodia/ca.crt version server
.EE
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B version
Print local build metadata and exit without contacting the server.
.TP
.B version server
Print server build metadata from
.BR /v1/version .
.TP
.B client create --client-id ID --mtls-subject SUBJECT
Register client metadata in the vault.
.TP
.B ca bootstrap-local --out-dir DIR --admin-client-id ID --server-name NAME
Generate Lite first-run CA material. The server certificate includes the requested
server name, localhost, 127.0.0.1, ::1 and any non-loopback IP address resolved
from the server name.
.TP
.B client sign-csr --client-id ID --csr-file FILE --certificate-out FILE --signer-url URL
Register client metadata, submit a client-generated CSR to
.BR custodia-signer (1),
and write the signed client certificate. The client mTLS private key stays on
the client host.
.TP
.B client csr --client-id ID --private-key-out FILE --csr-out FILE
Generate a local client mTLS private key and CSR. Prefer
.BR custodia-client " mtls generate-csr"
for remote client workstations.
.TP
.B client issue --client-id ID --out-dir DIR --signer-url URL
Register client metadata, generate local mTLS key/CSR, submit the CSR to
.BR custodia-signer (1),
extract the certificate, and create a local certificate bundle. This is a
convenience path for all-in-one Lite/lab hosts.
.TP
.B certificate sign --client-id ID --csr-file FILE
Submit a CSR to the signing service.
.TP
.B certificate extract --input FILE --certificate-out FILE
Extract a certificate PEM from signer JSON output.
.TP
.B certificate bundle --certificate FILE --private-key FILE --ca FILE --out FILE
Create a local ZIP bundle containing client mTLS material.
.TP
.B audit export
Export bounded audit metadata.
.TP
.B audit verify-export
Verify exported audit body/digest/count artifacts.
.TP
.B production check
Run production configuration checks from an environment file.
.TP
.B web totp configure --config FILE [--issuer NAME] [--account NAME]
Generate first-run Web MFA material, append it to the server YAML config, print
the TOTP secret and provisioning URI, and print a terminal QR code when
.B qrencode
is available.
.TP
.B doctor --server-config FILE --signer-config FILE [--systemd] [--network]
Run read-only installation diagnostics. The default mode is offline and checks
configuration parsing, profile/backend coherence, required files, key modes and
runtime directories. Optional flags add systemd unit checks and TCP listener
reachability checks.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --server-url " URL"
Custodia API base URL.
.TP
.BI --cert " FILE"
Admin mTLS client certificate.
.TP
.BI --key " FILE"
Admin mTLS private key.
.TP
.BI --ca " FILE"
Custodia CA certificate.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_BASE_URL
Default API base URL.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_ADMIN_CERT
Default admin certificate path.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_ADMIN_KEY
Default admin private key path.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_CA_CERT
Default CA certificate path.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SIGNER_URL
Default signer URL for client certificate issue workflows.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/admin.crt
Default local admin mTLS certificate.
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/admin.key
Default local admin mTLS private key. Keep readable only by root/custodia.
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/ca.crt
Default Custodia CA certificate.
.TP
.I /var/log/custodia/
Default server and signer log directory for packaged installs.
.SH SECURITY NOTES
.B custodia-admin
must not handle secret plaintext, DEKs, recipient envelopes, or application
private encryption keys. It is an administrative metadata and certificate
workflow tool.
.PP
Prefer running commands that read
.I /etc/custodia/admin.key
as the
.B custodia
service user instead of unrestricted root.
.SH EXAMPLES
Sign a client-generated CSR without handling the client mTLS private key on the server:
.PP
.EX
export CLIENT_ID=client_alice
export ISSUE_DIR="/var/lib/custodia/client-issue/$CLIENT_ID"
sudo rm -rf "$ISSUE_DIR"
sudo install -d -o custodia -g custodia -m 0700 "$ISSUE_DIR"
sudo install -o custodia -g custodia -m 0644 "$CLIENT_ID.csr" "$ISSUE_DIR/$CLIENT_ID.csr"
sudo -u custodia custodia-admin \
  --server-url https://localhost:8443 \
  --cert /etc/custodia/admin.crt \
  --key /etc/custodia/admin.key \
  --ca /etc/custodia/ca.crt \
  client sign-csr \
  --signer-url https://localhost:9444 \
  --client-id "$CLIENT_ID" \
  --csr-file "$ISSUE_DIR/$CLIENT_ID.csr" \
  --certificate-out "$ISSUE_DIR/$CLIENT_ID.crt"
sudo rm -rf "$ISSUE_DIR"
.EE

Configure first-run Web TOTP material in the server YAML:
.PP
.EX
sudo custodia-admin web totp configure \
  --config /etc/custodia/custodia-server.yaml \
  --account admin
.EE
.SH VERSION
Custodia version: @VERSION@
.br
Build commit: @COMMIT@
.br
Build date: @DATE@
.PP
Runtime version is available with:
.PP
.EX
custodia-admin version
.EE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Runtime or API failure.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR docs/DOCTOR.md ,
.BR custodia-client (1),
.BR custodia-server (1),
.BR custodia-signer (1)
